value.title: 'Unfair' Donald Trump can't complain: Imagine if another candidate acted like he does

value.title: Election 2020 live updates: Trump, Biden blitz swing states on election eve

value.title: 'You are no longer my mother': A divided America will struggle to heal after Trump era
value.excerpt: When lifelong Democrat Mayra Gomez told her 21-year-old son five months ago that she was voting for Donald Trump in Tuesday's presidential election, he cut her out of his life.

value.title: The Health 202: Obamacare marketplaces survived Trump's term better than expected
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is presiding over what could be its final Obamacare enrollment season, which started yesterday. As Election Day approaches, it's clear the much-hyped changes the administration made to the health insurance marketplaces over the past four years had far less impact — either positive or negative — than expected.

value.title: Why the math in Minnesota is more daunting for Trump than in 2016
value.excerpt: Nothing in the data suggests Donald Trump will win Minnesota. Coronavirus cases are surging. The early vote looks great for Democrats, who have swamped Trump’s ad spending in the state. But the contest appears to have tightened slightly in recent days.

value.title: Trump is touting the record-shattering GDP report as evidence of a full economic rebound. Here's why the recovery actually has much further to go.
value.excerpt: The US economy grew 7.4% in Q3, or 33.1% at an annualized rate. Many economists say growth is slowing down without another stimulus package.

value.title: Wisconsin GOP says hackers stole $2.3M from Trump reelection fund
